      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i'm not actually looking for the \"balance\" arguments right now. i need help building the case for the libertarian side. what are the most robust philosophical ways to argue that even \"harm prevention\" is a slippery slope that inevitably leads to censorship? give me the heavy hitters on the side of minimal regulation.",
